comments.body:
I meant that current ConverterUtils#toContainerId can parse the string you mentioned:

{code}
    ContainerId cid4 =
        ConverterUtils.toContainerId(
            "container_1410901177871_0001_01_000005_17");
    assertEquals(18691697672197L, cid4.getContainerId()); // it works well.
    assertEquals(5, cid4.getId()); // it works well.
{code}

Thanks for the comments and suggestion, Jian and Vinod.

[~jianhe] OK, I'll add the comment in a next patch.

{quote}
my fourth preference is to have something like container_1410901177871_0001_01_000005_e17, the first three preferences are what I proposed above 
{quote}
[~vinodkv] I agree with changing the verbose prefix to "e". I think {{container_1410901177871_0001_01_000005_e17}} looks best way - it's human readable, easy to implement, and can be parsed with old ConverterUtil. I'll update a patch based on the approach.
